      • JCEKSKeystoreCredentialStore

        public JCEKSKeystoreCredentialStore(String path,
                                    String passwordStr)
                             throws IOException
        Instantiate a new keystore at the given path protected by a password.
        Parameters:
        path - Path to find the keystore
        passwordStr - Password the keystore is protected with
        Throws:
        IOException - If the keystore cannot be loaded because the password is wrong or the file has been corrupted.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the keystore does not exist at the given path.

      • JCEKSKeystoreCredentialStore

        public JCEKSKeystoreCredentialStore(String path,
                                    String passwordStr,
                                    EnumSet<JCEKSKeystoreCredentialStore.CreationOptions> options)
                             throws IOException
        Instantiate a new keystore at the given path protected by a password.
        Parameters:
        path - Path to find the keystore
        passwordStr - Password the keystore is protected with
        options - Flags for keystore creation
        Throws:
        IOException - If the keystore cannot be loaded because of a corrupt file or the password is wrong
        IllegalArgumentException - If CREATE_IF_MISSING is not present in options and the keystore does not exist at the given path.

      • generateAesKeys

        public void generateAesKeys(int numKeys,
                            int startOffset)
                     throws IOException,
                            KeyStoreException
        Generate a set of AES keys for the store. The key ids will simple be (startOffset ... startOffset + numKeys).
        Parameters:
        numKeys - Number of keys to generate
        startOffset - ID to start generating keys with
        Throws:
        IOException - If there is an error serializing the keystore back to disk
        KeyStoreException - If there is an error serializing the keystore back to disk
